Here’s another little video of my disembodied hands altering a shirt🤗  I removed the cuff and placket to shorten the sleeves, and now I’m putting the placket back in. I love these two piece plackets on @etonshirts, they are super easy to alter🪡💙 The key is turning the sleeve inside out before sewing. I also like to press a crease along the slit line, it is helpful for positioning the point of the tower placket so that it doesn’t veer off at an angle 🏆🕺🏻 #lladybirdtailor #lladybirdprotips

I love me a huge life-changing alteration, but sometimes short and sweet is fun too! 🍉❤️
.
I bought this @alc_ltd piece at my work on DEEP discount. It actually started out as shorts (see pic #2), which I just could not get behind, and the waistband was weirdly really wide with this strange paper bag ruffly top (just no). But I thought it might work as a skirt, with a narrower waistband. I redrew the CF and CB seams so they were straight - easy! (Pic #3) Then I folded down the waistband by about 2” and stitched it down (pic #4). The original waistband is shirred - I just folded it down and stretched to the max while sewing a straight line on my machine. The piece is faux leather but I didn’t use any special feet, machines, nothing. Just about an hour of my time and now I have a cute little skirt! 💃🏻
.
That’s it, that’s the whole post. For more riveting alteration tips and trips and life changing overhauls, join one of my Alter + Repair classes! 🤗Alterations aren’t just about shortening lengths and taking in side seams - there’s also a super fun artistic side that will totally revamp your wardrobe and make your shit work for YOU and YOUR BODY and YOUR LIFESTYLE 👏 These classes sell out fast but I’ve still got a couple seats at @urbansewciety later this month! For more info (including other upcoming dates) check out my #linkinbio. Happy Saturday! ☀️ #madebylladybird #lladybird2023 #lladybirdtailor #llearningwithlladybird #sustainablesewing

✨What I’ve been working on✨
.
I bought a new sewing machine - and I’m learning Chainstitch Embroidery! 🤓🪡 I’ve been wanting to get into chain stitching for years - it looks so fun! So at the beginning of the year, I bit the very expensive bullet and got myself a new Consew 104-1T 🤗
.
Chainstitch embroidery is NOTHING like regular sewing. I’m starting entirely from scratch as I learn to maneuver this tricky machine (you turn a crank under the machine to rotate your work!), and it has been a VERY steep learning curve. I’m a pretty good self learner, but I decided to invest in my Chainstitch future with online lessons from @huckmade_dot_com. Huckleberry is an incredible teacher - experienced, patient, and he really knows his shit. I highly recommend him if you are looking for some guidance with your chainstitching. I learned so many little tricks that absolutely blew my mind, and plan on continuing my lessons with him as I build my skills 💪🏻
.
It’s been about a month and a half since I started, and while I’m still veryyyy strongly in the beginner category, I’m really starting to see improvement! Which is exciting! This weekend I started writing script (instead of swirly lines lol) and I’m impressed that it’s actually legible🤠 Can only get better from here! Cheers for learning new things - and the humble feeling of being an absolute, terrible beginner at something🥰 #lladybird2023

This weekend I took the sleeves off this @deer_and_doe_patterns Magnolia dress and it is suddenly soooo much more wearable! 💪🏻😍I liked those circular flutter sleeves - swipe to see a before - but I never wanted to wear the dress. Something about the proportions always felt off to me, not to mention it’s hard to wrangle those sleeves under a jacket or cardigan. I’ve probably worn this shit twice since I finished it a few years ago. So I cut those bad boys off and finished the edges with bias facing. I also took the opportunity to pull up the front neckline, as it was gaping a little 🤠 I LOVE this rayon from @workroomsocial and I’m so happy I finally feel comfortable and cute in the dress I made using it! 🥰 #lladybird2023 #lladybirdtailor #workroomsocialfabrics #ddmagnolia

Introducing The Banana Bag!🍌🍌🍌
.
I made this sling bag using the #fennelfannypack pattern and some fun quilting cotton from @fancytigercrafts . I changed the pattern to be about 1/2” deeper, added a small interior pocket (perfect for credit cards, or teeny little things that otherwise get lost) and used a double pull zipper across the top to make it easier to sneak in the bag without dumping out the entire contents (story of my life). The outer cotton is fully interfaced with medium weight craft fusible 💪🏻
.
I messed up the front zipper, and while unpicking in a hurry (don’t do this y’all), I tore a hole in the fabric 😫 My patch solution was to hand embroider a lil smiling banana right over the tear! 🙃 Now it’s not a mistake- it’s a DESIGN ELEMENT🕺🏻
.
I actually made this bag multiple months ago and have carried it regularly since (it’s basically my purse) - hence the worn and dirty spots! Whatever, that’s real life baby! 💯 I love that I can wear it across my body (front or back) or on my hip. It is especially perfect for travel and working on set - a handy extra pocket! And I love that I went with this goofy smiling banana fabric, instead of something neutral and grown up. It’s a fanny pack, it is gonna look fucking silly no matter what it’s made out of. Might as well embrace the weird🤓 #madebylladybird #lladybird2023 #bananabag #itsafannypacknotabeltbag

Sharing some Alterations Magic today⭐️🪄✨!
.
I have these @agolde jeans that I love, but the waist gets stretched as the day goes on - so they eventually droop and hang below my crotch (boo). I’m taking a vacation in a couple months and was hoping to bring them, but considering I can really only get 1 wear before washing, I really needed to re-evaluate that waistband situation! I didn’t want to simply take in the waistband as I usually do (making a seam at the center back and stretching the waistband to fit), because I like that it is comfortably loose. I just didn’t want it to stretch so much it causes the pants to fall down.
.
So - I put elastic in them! And you can’t even tell! (See: butt photos 🩷 Do not: make gross comments🙅🏻‍♀️❌) 
.
I opened up the back waistband and sandwiched the elastic in, anchoring it down with new topstitching at the top and bottom. I was able to take 1.25” out of the waistband and you cannot tell there is elastic back there - it just stretches out flat when I’m wearing the pants. It is a slightly thicker, but not noticeably so. Even better - since I didn’t actually cut anything, I can always remove the elastic and revert the pants waistband back to its original size if needed!💪🏻 As of this post, I have successfully gotten 4 days wear out of my jeans, with no waistband sliding. Like I said - alterations are MAGIC, y’all! 🧙🏻‍♀️🌟
.
Want to learn more alterations tips, tricks, hacks, and brilliant ideas? Just recently discovered that you can totally replace the blade on these @bohin_france folding seam rippers 🤠 I pull out the blade with pliers and replace it with the blade from the cheap blue ones. I replace my seam rippers often - two or three times a month - and this is more economical than buying a whole new folding ripper 💸💸💸 BTW most seam rippers use the same type of blade - the real difference that you’re paying for is the handle. I like these handles the best because they fit in my hands nicely and that folding action makes the most satisfying click🤤 #lladybirdprotips #llearningwithlladybird

Just some fun lil snaps from my trip to Peru last month 🤩 It was almost impossible to narrow them down to 10 (which is kind of wild because I honestly didn’t take a ton of pictures on this trip!), so I’ll share the weird non-touristy ones in another post 🥸
.
Most of my trip was spent in Urubamba, which was magical. I met @claudiarulz my first morning there and we had an amazing day exploring the Sacred Valley and accidentally going into areas where we weren’t allowed 🌚 I visited Pisaq, Moray, the Salt Mines, climbed a mountain trail to the chullpas in Urubamba, and of course saw Machu Picchu (and had the best tour guide who took some serious glamor shots of me lmaoooo). Mostly, I spent a lot of time freaking out over the landscapes and the plants. I lied, I took a lot of photos but they were mostly of plants haha 🍃
.
Oh, and I flew first class so even my flight was a fun experience! Peep all that unused leg room ahead of my LAY-FLAT seat, ha! ✈️
.
Peru is one of my favorite countries and I’m so glad I had the opportunity to go back and see a different side this time 🥰 Definitely won’t be my last trip! I’ve been working on my Spanish, and while I’m still incredibly limited in my communication I *was* able to order breakfast one morning and also tell someone my age, so, I’ll count those as a win lol 🇵🇪
A little bit of random Peru for your Saturday morning 🌞 As a side note, I really wish I had that floral window grate in photo 7. It would be so cute on my house! 🌻

A handful of weird + wonderful jeans details courtesy of my camera roll 🤩📸 This is the kind of shit you never notice until you make your own jeans - then you can’t not see it 🙃  BTW those trouser-jeans hybrid in the last photos are from @zegnaofficial and yes they DO have a bound buttonhole 😆💸

My 2023 in picture review! I was going to post a few photos, but I had too many for a slideshow so y’all get a video (complete with annoying music from my teenage years) instead 😇 
.
2023 was a great year for me! I taught 14 weekends worth of workshops🪡👖, took a solo trip to Peru🇵🇪, got my flower gardens looking FINE🌸, bought + learned how to use my chainstitch embroidery machine🕺🏻, and spent a ton of time with my family (including a new great-nephew👼🏼). And, of course, I made some neat shit (only some of it featured here), both for myself and for some fun clients 🤠
.
This year, I made a deliberate choice to spend less time on social media - the scrolling was making me feel bad, and the posting was stressing me out. Best decision ever and I highly recommend if the feeds are making you feel crummy 🌚🌝 BTW this dumb video took me like 2 hours to assemble, so I hope you enjoy it and don’t expect more!😆
.
Excited to see what 2024 brings! Happy New Year, everyone! ✨💯
